Let me go.
GREGORY.
I can't.
I have no will.
Something stronger than either of us is in command here.
Nothing on earth or in heaven can part us now.
You know that, don't you?
MRS. JUNO.
Oh, don't make me say it.
Of course I know.
Nothing—not life nor death nor shame nor anything can part us.
A MATTER-OF-FACT MALE VOICE IN THE CORRIDOR.
All right.
