JUNO [officiously] Ah: here we are.
[He leads the way to the sofa].
Sit down: I'm sure you're tired.
[She sits].
That's right.
[He sits beside her on her left].
Hullo!
[he rises] this sofa's quite warm.
MRS. LUNN [bored] Is it?
I don't notice it.
I expect the sun's been on it.
JUNO.
I felt it quite distinctly: I'm more thinly clad than you.
[He sits down again, and proceeds, with a sigh of satisfaction].
